	<h1 id="main-heading">KRS ยง 189.231 - State maintained highways; restriction and regulation of traffic</h1>

	<ol class="flow law-definitions">
		<li>The secretary of transportation may install and maintain traffic control devices upon state-maintained highways in such manner as is reasonably necessary to promote the safety and convenience of the traveling public.</li>
		<li>The driver of any vehicle shall obey the instructions of any official traffic control device applicable thereto unless otherwise directed by a traffic or police officer, subject to the exceptions granted the driver of an authorized emergency vehicle.</li>
		<li>The secretary of transportation may restrict or regulate traffic upon state-maintained highways in such a manner as is reasonably necessary to promote the safety of the traveling public.</li>
	</ol>

